HEADWORD: Bolden
<hw>Bold"en</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Boldened</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. ]</vmorph> <def>To
make bold; to encourage; to embolden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ready speakers, being <qex>boldened</qex> with their present
abilities to say more, . . . use less help of diligence and study.</q>
<rj><qau>Ascham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

